      "Tips": [
        {
          "Text": "Iron cannot be teleported — set up a smelting outpost near the Swamp or sail it home by boat",
          "Category": "general",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Blunt damage is king in the Swamp — Skeletons, Blobs, and Bonemass all resist Slash and Pierce",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
                {
          "Text": "Dragon Eggs weigh 200kg each and cannot be teleported — haul all 3 to Moder's altar before you start the fight",
          "Category": "general",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "The Wolf Fur Cape or Lox Cape negates the freezing debuff permanently — craft one before exploring the peaks",
          "Category": "general",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Dig a trench near Moder's altar before summoning — her ice projectiles cannot angle downward into it",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Wolves can be tamed with raw meat — bred wolves produce wolf cubs and eventually Wolf Pelt without hunting",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Stone Golems are immune to all damage types except blunt and pickaxe — a Bronze Pickaxe works fine",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "The Silver physics pop: dig completely under a Silver vein until it floats, hit the centre — it collapses into loose ore instantly",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Turnip seeds look like wispy yellow flowers in the Swamp — you only need one plant to start your farm",
          "Category": "gathering",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Equip any Warhammer/Stagbreaker and smash the ground in the Swamp — a 0 damage hit means buried iron underneath",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Wraiths only spawn at night and drop Chains — needed to upgrade the Forge and craft Wolf Armor later",
          "Category": "gathering",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Killing an Abomination and crafting the Root Mask gives permanent poison resistance — no more potions needed",
          "Category": "secret",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Flatten the ground around the Bonemass skull with a Hoe before summoning — you do not want to fight in water",
          "Category": "building",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Poison Resistance Mead is mandatory for Bonemass — drink it before summoning, not during the fight",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Don't throw away Draugr Entrails — combine with Raw Meat and Thistle at a Cauldron to make Sausages",
          "Category": "gathering",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Enter the Swamp with a Bronze Mace — most enemies resist Slash and Pierce, but Blunt damage shreds them",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Max-upgrade your Bronze Buckler before entering — parrying Draugr opens them up for massive counter damage",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "The Stagbreaker's AoE ground slam kills Leeches from the shore and bursts Blobs before they can jump on you",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "Once you have Iron, craft the Iron Mace first — it is practically required to fight Bonemass",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        },
        {
          "Text": "The Huntsman Bow has a smaller aggro radius than the Finewood Bow — use it to snipe Draugr without waking the camp",
          "Category": "combat",
          "ModRequired": null
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}